==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[molimen]] ‘effort’, from [[moliri]] ‘make an effort’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /mə'lɪmɪnəs/

===Adjective===
'''moliminous'''
# [[laborious]], involving or exerting great effort; [[momentous]]
#:*'''1985''': All natural logick of expression in the elements is made thereby interrupted and most obscure, howe’er so skilled and '''moliminous''' the adeptist. — John Fowles, ''A Maggot''